                    <p>We had been always using <a href="https://drupal.org/project/faq">FAQ module</a> to create Frequently Asked Questions for any of our projects. But on our latest theme, <a href="/drupal-theme/bizreview">BizReview</a>, we switch to a new module, <a href="https://www.drupal.org/project/faqfield">FAQ Field</a>.</p>
        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<p><strong>FAQ</strong> is a classic module, it is there since Drupal 6. So when we have to build a FAQ section, using this module is a no brainer. This is the FAQ module in action on our <a href="http://demo.symphonythemes.com/drupal7/velocity/faq-page">Velocity</a> theme.</p>
